Jack Ma, the founder of Alibaba, had a vision to help small businesses in China reach global markets. By providing them with an online platform, he democratized access to international trade. This was revolutionary at a time when traditional trade required significant resources and connections.

Alibaba also invested heavily in technology and logistics to support its growth. For example, it developed Alipay, an online payment system, which reduced the risks associated with online transactions and boosted trust between buyers and sellers.

